VendingMachine 1 -- * slots Dispenser
A Dispenser called slots has A VendingMachine. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one VendingMachine.
A VendingMachine has some Dispensers called slots. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Dispenser is created, its VendingMachine must be assigned. When a Dispenser is deleted, its VendingMachine is not deleted and its list of Dispensers is decreased. When a VendingMachine is deleted, its Dispensers are not deleted. They are assigned to another VendingMachine.
